body: @mzmssg : What version of onnxruntime and execution provider are you ?
It is a known bug that many fusions check GetOutputEdgesCount() != 1 to see whether a subgraph can be fused but graph output is not counted in output edges. It is in our back log.

issue.title: Add check of graph output in Bert Fusions

labels.name: model:transformer
labels.description: issues related to a transformer model: BERT, GPT2, Hugging Face, Longformer, T5, etc.

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**: 

Node.GetOutputEdges() does not include graph output. Additional check is added for each internal node (in a subgraph to be fused): Do not fuse if internal node has graph output.

**Motivation and Context**
- Why is this change required? What problem does it solve?
- If it fixes an open issue, please link to the issue here.

Address the bug in issues https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/4110

body:
@tianleiwu : Thanks for adding the PR to add the check for graph outputs

I am debugging the first issue mentioned here : "Inference session output differently with/without optimization"

This is because BiasGelu fusion has a bug... It is not adding correct bias input for this node. In the cpu implementation we have a check to verify the dimension of bias which fails and it errors out... In cuda implementation we do not have this check because of which the inference continues and the end result is wrong.

BiasGelu:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6475296/83716483-e4531c80-a5e4-11ea-8a36-e8ece88db368.png)


CPU Execution Provider error: 
Name:'BiasGelu' Status Message: Input 1 is expected to have 1 dimensions, got 3

PR on the way

issue.title: Fix for BiasGelu fusion optimizer

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**: BiasGelu optimizer allows input switching based on the dimension of the inputs. .i.e after converting eligible subgraph to BiasGelu node it will pick the input with dim size == 1 as the 2nd input for the node and the left over input as the 1rst input. 
There is a bug in how the input edges are created for the optimized graph when input switching is applied. This PR fixes the bug. 

**Motivation and Context**
- Fixes the first issue mentioned in : https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/4110
